<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910301-0029</DOCNO><DOCID>910301-0029.</DOCID><HL>   McDonnell Douglas   Subsidiary to Pay U.S.   Fine of $7.5 Million</HL><DATE>03/01/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C8</SO><CO>   MD</CO><IN>AEROSPACE (ARO)</IN><GV>JUSTICE DEPARTMENT (JUS)DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF)</GV><LP>   WASHINGTON -- The Justice Department said a McDonnellDouglas Corp. unit agreed to pay the government a $7.5million civil fine in a claim relating to a 1983 contract forthe purchase of an externally powered automatic gun, known asthe M-242.   The gun is primarily used on the Army's Bradley fightingvehicle. The Justice Department said McDonnell Douglas'sHughes Helicopter Inc. unit gave the Army &quot;greatly inflatedcosts for many of the components of the gun, resulting in anexcessively high contract price.&quot; McDonnell Douglas, theJustice Department said, settled the matter without admittingthat it supplied false data to the Army.</LP><TEXT>   A McDonnell Douglas spokesman said the company couldn'timmediately comment on the government's announcement.</TEXT></DOC>